<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2105] All appends are serialized in HLog</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2105</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;duiod on IRC was asking about locks on the write path so I reviewed it a bit and saw that we are very good at not locking except on row level in HRegion and others but in HLog we actually synchronize everything on updateLock. I&apos;m pretty sure that&apos;s not what we want. I guess a RWLock would be more useful.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12445201">HBASE-2105</key>
            <summary>All appends are serialized in HLog</summary>
